B.ab2=new A.bN("Grammar","I Before E",'"I before E, except after C, or when sounding like A as in neighbor and weigh."','Kata dengan "ie" biasanya: believe, field, thief. Kecuali setelah C: receive, ceiling. Atau \u0437\u0432\u0443\u043a /e\u026a/: eight, weight, neighbor.',"believe (i-e), receive (e-i setelah c), weight (e-i \u0437\u0432\u0443\u043a /e\u026a/)")
B.abl=new A.bN("Grammar","Subject-Verb Agreement - FANBOYS",'"FANBOYS" = For, And, Nor, But, Or, Yet, So. Kata-kata ini memerlukan koma sebelumnya.'," Coordinating conjunctions (FANBOYS) menggabungkan dua independent clauses dengan koma sebelumnya.","I wanted to go, but he refused. She studied hard, yet she failed.")
B.ab0=new A.bN("Grammar","Commas with FANBOYS",'"FANBOYS always needs a comma before it."',"Setiap kali menggunakan For, And, Nor, But, Or, Yet, So untuk menggabungkan dua kalimat lengkap, letakkan koma sebelumnya.","We can go now, and we can wait here. Not: We can go now and we can wait here.")
B.abj=new A.bN("Grammar","Who vs Whom",'"Who is like HE. Whom is like HIM."','Jika bisa ganti dengan "he/him" di kalimat, gunakan who/whom yang sesuai. "Who is he?" / "Whom did you see?" -> "You saw HIM."',"Who is calling? ( \u0441\u0443\u0431\u044a\u0435\u043a\u0442 ) | Whom are you waiting for? ( \u043e\u0431\u044a\u0435\u043a\u0442 )")
B.aaY=new A.bN("Grammar","Principal Parts of Verb",'"Base form, past, past participle - keep them all quite ample."',"Ingat tiga bentuk utama verb untuk irregular verbs. Contoh: go - went - gone, see - saw - seen, eat - ate - eaten.","go-went-gone | see-saw-seen | write-wrote-written | swim-swam-swum")
B.abd=new A.bN("Spelling","Necessary",'"One collar and two sleeves" -Necessary memiliki satu c dan dua r.','Ne-ce-ss-a-ry = hanya ada satu s setelah ce. Pola "ss" tidak ada di sini.',"ne-CESS-ary (bukan ne-CESS-ary). Huruf kapital menunjukkan double letter.")
B.abu=new A.bN("Spelling","Separate",'"SepaRATe - rats SEPA rate through the word."','"Separate" bukan "seperate". Ada SEPA di awal dan RATE di akhir. Rats tidak punya double letter.',"separate - SEPA + RATE. Bukan: seperate, seperat, sepperate.")
B.abr=new A.bN("Spelling","Accommodate","\"ACcommodate: 2 C's and 2 M's - ACCOMMODATE.\"","Accommodate memiliki double C dan double M. Bayangkan dua kamar (CC) dan dua kasur (MM).","accommodate - a-c-c-o-m-m-o-d-a-t-e. Bukan: acommodate, acomodate.")
B.abo=new A.bN("Spelling","Definitely",'"Definitely has a tree in it." - DEF(i)NITELY.','Banyak orang menulis "definately" (salah). Perhatikan ada "i" sebelum "nitely" dan TIDAK ada huruf A.',"definitely - D-E-F-I-N-I-T-E-L-Y. Bukan: definately, definetly.")
B.ab5=new A.bN("Spelling","Misspell",'"There is a MISS in MISSpell."','Trik lucu: kata "misspell" sendiri punya MISS di dalamnya, mengingatkan bahwa kata ini sering misspelled.',"misspell (benar). Mistakes: mispel, msispel, mispell.")
B.ab3=new A.bN("Spelling","Tomorrow",'"Tomorrow has MOO in it - Like a cow, it will come MOO-re and MOO-re!"','Tomorrow = to-mor-row. Ada "mor" yang berbunyi seperti "more". Panjang dan penuh harapan.',"tomorrow (bukan tommorow, tomorow, tomorrow).")
B.abv=new A.bN("Spelling","Embarrass","\"EmbarrASS - Two R's and two S's. You will be embarrassed remembering this.\"","Embarrass = em-bar-rass. Double R, double S. Seperti malu yang ganda-ganda.","embarrass (bukan embarrase, embaras, embares).")
B.ab6=new A.bN("Spelling","Rhythm",'"RHythm helps your HEART -ythm, ythm. Miss one and your heart breaks."',"Rhythm = R-H-Y-T-H-M. Huruf H dan Y adalah teman. Tanpa salah satu, irama hancur.","rhythm (bukan ryhthm, rhtyhm, rhythm).")
B.abg=new A.bN("Spelling","Calendar",'"Calendar has LENT in it - and a calendar LENDS you time."',"Calendar = C-A-L-E-N-D-A-R. Huruf D dan A setelah LENT. Calendar lends you days.","calendar (bukan calender, calandar, callendar).")
B.abk=new A.bN("Spelling","Occur",'"Occur has two C\'s because things can OCCUR more than once."',"Occur = o-c-c-u-r. Double C untuk mengingatkan bahwa sesuatu bisa terjadi berulang kali.","occur, occurred, occurring (bukan accur, ocure, occur).")
B.abA=new A.bN("Vocabulary","Heterogeneous",'"HETERO-geneous - HETERO = different, geneous = kind. Different kinds inside."',"Heterogeneous = terdiri dari berbagai jenis yang berbeda. Lawannya: homogeneous.","A heterogeneous mixture contains different substances. (berbeda-beda)")
B.abp=new A.bN("Vocabulary","Ephemeral",'"Eph-em-er-al - Emphatically short life. Like an EPHEmist who lives briefly."','Ephemeral = berlangsung singkat, cepat menghilang. Dari bahasa Yunani "ephemeros" = harian/separuh hari.',"Fame in social media can be ephemeral. (sementara, fana)")
B.abb=new A.bN("Vocabulary","Ubiquitous",'"Ubi-quitous - Ubi = everywhere, quitous = ??? Ubiquitous = everywhere!"','Ubiquitous = ada di mana-mana. Dari Latin "ubique" = everywhere. WiFi terasa ubiquitous di kota.',"Smartphones have become ubiquitous. (\u65e0\u5904\u4e0d\u5728, ada di mana-mana)")
B.abc=new A.bN("Vocabulary","Amateur",'"AMateur - AMateur = person who does something for the AM (love), not money."','Amateur = pemula, bukan profesional. Dari Latin "amator" = \u043b\u044e\u0431\u0438\u0442\u0435\u043b\u044c. Melakukan sesuatu karena cinta, bukan uang.',"Don't be an amateur; practice makes perfect. (pemula, amatur)")
B.ab1=new A.bN("Vocabulary","Anomaly",'"An-omaly - Something that is AN OMLY (only) - it stands out from normal."','Anomaly = penyimpangan dari normal. Ada satu aturan yang dilanggar. Dari Yunani "anomalia" = ketidakreguleran.',"This warm weather in winter is an anomaly. (penyimpangan, keanehan)")
B.abn=new A.bN("Vocabulary","Belligerent",'"BELLIgerent - Like going to WAR (bellum in Latin = war). Belligerent = war-like."','Belligerent = suka berkelahi, agresif. Dari Latin "bellum" = perang. Orang yang belligerent suka memulai perang.',"The belligerent customer refused to calm down. (suka berkelahi, agresif)")
B.abi=new A.bN("Vocabulary","Capricious",'"CAPrious - Like a CAPRICE or a goat (caper in Latin = goat). Goats jump unpredictably!"','Capricious = berubah-ubah, tidak menentu. Dari Latin "caper" = goat. Kambing suka melompat tak terduga.',"Her capricious nature made planning difficult. (suka berubah-ubah, tidak tetap)")
B.aba=new A.bN("Vocabulary","Diligent",'"DILIgence - DILIgence = working hard and CAREFUL. Only one L!"','Diligent = rajin, tekun. Dari Latin "diligens" = careful. Jangan salah: hanya ada satu L, bukan dua.',"Diligent students always complete their homework on time. (rajin, tekun)")
B.aby=new A.bN("Vocabulary","Eloquent",'"ELOquent - Speaking so beautifully that everyone LISTENS. E-LO-quent."','Eloquent = fasih, berbicara dengan baik dan meyakinkan. Dari Latin "eloquentia" = seni berbicara.',"The lawyer gave an eloquent closing statement. (fasih,\uff0c\u534e\u4e3d)")
B.abq=new A.bN("Vocabulary","Gregarious",'"GREGarious - GREG = group, arian = related to. Related to groups = sociable!"','Gregarious = suka bergaul, ramah. Dari Latin "greg" = kawanan/flock. Seperti domba yang hidup berkelompok.',"She is very gregarious and makes friends easily. (suka bergaul, ramah)")
B.abf=new A.bN("Pronunciation","-ough Pronunciations",'"A rough, tough cough through the slough should give you enough. Though, thoughtful!"',"-ough punya banyak \u0437\u0432\u0443\u043a: rough /r\u028cf/, tough /t\u028cf/, cough /k\u0252f/, through /\u03b8ru\u02d0/, though /\xf0o\u028a/, thought /\u03b8\u0254\u02d0t/. Tidak ada polanya!","rough-tough-cough-through(\u03b8ru\u02d0)-though(\xf0o\u028a)-thought-borough")
B.ab7=new A.bN("Pronunciation","Colonel",'"COLONEL - Tapi dibaca KERNEL!"','Colonel (/k\u025c\u02d0rn\u0259l/) dieja dengan O tapi dibaca seperti ER. Dari bahasa Italia "colonello". Jangan percaya hurufnya!',"Colonel Sanders | The colonel arrived late. (diucapkan /k\u025c\u02d0rn\u0259l/)")
B.abs=new A.bN("Pronunciation","Psychology",'"PSYCHOLOGY - Silent P, PSY start. Like a PSYcho\'s LOGY."','Psychology dieja P-S-Y-C-H-O-L-O-G-Y. Huruf P di awal TIDAK dibaca. Suara ada di PSY- untuk mengingatkan "psycho".',"She studied psychology at university. (/sa\u026a\u02c8k\u0252l\u0259d\u0292i/)")
B.abh=new A.bN("Pronunciation","Wednesday",'"WED-nes-day - WED adalah kunci. Bukan WENS-day!"','Wednesday dieja W-E-D-N-E-S-D-A-Y tapi dibaca /\u02c8wenzde\u026a/. Huruf D di "wed" harus terdengar, tapi sering dilupakan.',"Wednesday is hump day. (dieja Wednesday, dibaca /\u02c8wenzde\u026a/)")
B.ab9=new A.bN("Pronunciation","Suite",'"SUITE - Dieja seperti SWEET tapi untuk kamar hotel."',"Suite (/swi\u02d0t/) dan sweet (/swi\u02d0t/) berbunyi sama! Suite adalah kamar hotel premium atau set furniture.","We booked a suite at the hotel. (berbunyi sama dengan sweet)")
B.ab4=new A.bN("Memory","Parts of Speech Order",'"A BOLD FINGER came to my HOUSE." = Adverb, Adjective, Verb, Noun, Conjunction, Interjection, Preposition, Pronoun.'," gunakan sebagai pengingat urutan dalam analisis kalimat atau gramatika tradisional.","ADVERB + ADJECTIVE + BOLD + VERB + NOUN + CONJUNCTION + INTERJECTION + PRONOUN + PREPOSITION")
B.abm=new A.bN("Memory","Order of Planets",'"My Very Eager Mother Just Served Us Nine Pizzas" = Mercury, Venus, Earth, Mars, Jupiter, Saturn, Uranus, Neptune, Pluto.',"Urutkan planet dari yang paling dekat dengan matahari. Pluto sekarang tidak dianggap planet.","Mercury \u2192 Venus \u2192 Earth \u2192 Mars \u2192 Jupiter \u2192 Saturn \u2192 Uranus \u2192 Neptune")
B.abt=new A.bN("Memory","Five W's + H",'"When W-H-Y? Who What Where When How!"',"Untuk investigasi dan penulisan berita, selalu jawab: Who, What, Where, When, Why, How.","Who did it? What happened? Where? When? Why? How?")
B.abw=new A.bN("Memory","SM-2 Spaced Repetition",'"AGAIN HARD GOOD EASY = 0 1 2 3. Like climbing stairs: LOW to HIGH."',"Ingat lagi tombol di SRS: Again=reset, Hard=lebih pendek, Good=normal, Easy=lebih panjang. Rating naik = interval naik.","Again(0) \u2192 Hard(1) \u2192 Good(2) \u2192 Easy(3). Setiap tingkat menambah interval.")
B.ab8=new A.bN("Memory","Passive Voice Formula",'"SUBJECT + TO BE + PAST PARTICIPLE. S + Be + PP."',"Passive voice: ambil objek, tambahkan to be yang sesuai dengan tense, tambahkan past participle verb.","Active: The cat eats the fish. \u2192 Passive: The fish is eaten by the cat.")
B.abe=new A.bN("Memory","Countable vs Uncountable",'"Can you count it? WATER, MONEY, INFORMATION = cant be counted!"',"Uncountable nouns: water, money, information, advice, furniture, luggage, baggage, traffic. Gunakan MUCH/MANY dengan benar.","much water, much money, many friends, many books")
B.abx=new A.bN("Memory","Reported Speech Tenses",'"Tenses go BACK: will\u2192would, can\u2192could, shall\u2192should, may\u2192might."',"Dalam reported speech, tense umumnya mundur satu tingkat. Future \u2192 Conditional, Present \u2192 Past, Past \u2192 Past Perfect.",'"I will go" \u2192 He said he would go. "I can swim" \u2192 He said he could swim.')
B.ab_=new A.bN("Memory","Conditional Sentence Types",'"Type 1: REAL. Type 2: UNREAL/IMAGINARY. Type 3: IMPOSSIBLE PAST."',"Type 1: If + present, will + verb (mungkin terjadi). Type 2: If + past, would + verb (imajiner). Type 3: If + had + past participle, would have + verb (penyesalan masa lalu).","T1: If it rains, I will stay home. T2: If I were rich, I would travel. T3: If I had studied, I would have passed.")
B.abz=new A.bN("Memory","Comparative Superlative",'"SHORTER words: -er/-est. LONGER words: MORE/MOST."',"Kata pendek (1-2 suku): add -er/-est. Kata panjang (3+ suku): use more/most. Pengecualian: good-better-best, bad-worse-worst.","tall-taller-tallest | beautiful-more beautiful-most beautiful | good-better-best")
B.aaZ=new A.bN("Memory","Gerund vs Infinitive",'"LOVE/HATE/ENJOY/MIND + GERUND (like doing). WANT/DECIDE/PLAN + INFINITIVE (to do). Might/HOPE/EXPECT/WOULD LIKE + INFINITIVE."',"Beberapa verb memerlukan gerund (-ing), lainnya memerlukan infinitive (to + verb). Hafalkan kelompoknya.","I enjoy reading (gerund) | I decided to study (infinitive) | I would like to travel (infinitive)")
