B.SS=new A.bK("She don't like coffee.","She doesn't like coffee.",'Subjek singular "she" memerlukan "doesn\'t" (not don\'t). Jangan gunakan don\'t dengan she/he/it.',"Subject-Verb Agreement")
B.SF=new A.bK("Each of the students have a notebook.","Each of the students has a notebook.",'"Each" selalu memerlukan singular verb. Meskipun "students" plural, "each" mengambil singular.',"Subject-Verb Agreement")
B.ST=new A.bK("Neither my friends nor I am going.","Neither my friends nor I am going.",'Dengan "neither...nor", verb \u0441\u043e\u0433\u043b\u0430\u0441nya \u0441 \u043f\u043e\u0441\u043b\u0435\u0434\u043d\u0438\u043c \u044d\u043b\u0435\u043c\u0435\u043d\u0442\u043e\u043c. "I" adalah \u043f\u043e\u0441\u043b\u0435\u0434\u043d\u0438\u0439, jadi "am" benar.',"Subject-Verb Agreement")
B.SR=new A.bK("The team are playing well.","The team is playing well.",'"Team" adalah noun singular collective. Dalam American English, gunakan singular verb.',"Subject-Verb Agreement")
B.SL=new A.bK("There is many reasons to study.","There are many reasons to study.",'"Reasons" adalah plural, jadi gunakan "are" bukan "is".',"Subject-Verb Agreement")
B.SX=new A.bK("I have seen him yesterday.","I saw him yesterday.",'"Yesterday" memerlukan past simple, bukan present perfect.',"Tense Errors")
B.SA=new A.bK("She is working here since 2020.","She has been working here since 2020.",'Gunakan present perfect continuous (has been working) dengan "since" untuk aksi yang masih berlanjut.',"Tense Errors")
B.Td=new A.bK("If I had money, I will buy it.","If I had money, I would buy it.","Conditional type 2 memerlukan past simple di if-clause dan would di main clause.","Tense Errors")
B.Tb=new A.bK("I wish I am taller.","I wish I were taller.",'Setelah "wish", gunakan past simple untuk keinginan yang tidak realistis. "Were" digunakan untuk semua subjek.',"Tense Errors")
B.Ta=new A.bK("He has went to school.","He has gone to school.",'"Has gone" adalah past participle yang benar. "Went" adalah past simple, bukan participle.',"Tense Errors")
B.T6=new A.bK("She is a honest girl.","She is an honest girl.",'"An" digunakan sebelum kata yang dimulai dengan bunyi vokal. "Honest" berbunyi /onest/.',"Articles")
B.SP=new A.bK(u.M,u.M,'Benar. Namun perlu diingat: gunakan "an" untuk bunyi vokal, bukan huruf. "Umbrella" /umbrella/.',"Articles")
B.SY=new A.bK(u.O,u.O,'Benar. Gunakan "the most" untuk superlative degree dengan kata yang lebih dari dua suku.',"Articles")
B.T5=new A.bK("I went to hospital yesterday.","I went to the hospital yesterday.",'Dalam American English, gunakan article "the" dengan hospital, school, church, prison, dll ketika tujuannya bukan untuk berobat/menetap.',"Articles")
B.SD=new A.bK("She is studying for exam.","She is studying for an exam.",'Gunakan article "an" sebelum kata yang dimulai dengan bunyi vokal (/e/ dari exam).',"Articles")
B.SU=new A.bK("She arrived in Monday.","She arrived on Monday.",u.H,"Preposition")
B.SZ=new A.bK("I am good in mathematics.","I am good at mathematics.",u.b,"Preposition")
B.SN=new A.bK("She got married with a doctor.","She got married to a doctor.",'"Get married to" adalah collocation yang benar, bukan "with".',"Preposition")
B.T7=new A.bK("I will call you in the evening.","I will call you in the evening.",'"In" digunakan untuk bagian hari (morning, afternoon, evening, night). Tapi untuk waktu spesifik, gunakan "at" (at 5 o\'clock) atau "on" (on Monday).',"Preposition")
B.T3=new A.bK("He died from cancer.","He died of cancer.",'"Die of" digunakan untuk penyakit. "Die from" untuk causes yang lebih umum.',"Preposition")
B.T2=new A.bK("I am interesting in learning languages.","I am interested in learning languages.",'"Interested" adalah adjective yang diperlukan untuk menggambarkan perasaan. "Interesting" digunakan untuk menggambarkan benda/orang.',"Word Choice")
B.Tg=new A.bK("The movie was very frightened.","The movie was very frightening.",'"Frightening" digunakan untuk sesuatu yang menyebabkan ketakutan. "Frightened" untuk perasaan takut.',"Word Choice")
B.T4=new A.bK("She is very clever than her brother.","She is much cleverer than her brother.",'Gunakan comparative form dengan "than". Untuk membandingkan, gunakan -er atau "more" + adjective.',"Word Choice")
B.SV=new A.bK("I have fewer luggage than you.","I have less luggage than you.",'"Luggage" adalah uncountable noun, jadi gunakan "less" bukan "fewer".',"Word Choice")
B.SH=new A.bK("He is enough old to drive.","He is old enough to drive.",'"Enough" datang SETELAH adjective. Ketrangan: adjective + enough + to-infinitive.',"Word Choice")
B.T_=new A.bK("I need some informations.","I need some information.",'"Information" adalah uncountable noun. Gunakan "some information" tanpa -s.',"Countable/Uncountable")
B.Te=new A.bK("She gave me a good advice.","She gave me good advice.",'"Advice" adalah uncountable noun. Gunakan "some advice" atau "a piece of advice".',"Countable/Uncountable")
B.T9=new A.bK("I have many furnitures.","I have a lot of furniture.",'"Furniture" adalah uncountable noun. Gunakan "some furniture" atau "a piece of furniture".',"Countable/Uncountable")
B.SO=new A.bK("How many money do you have?","How much money do you have?",'"Money" adalah uncountable noun, jadi gunakan "how much" bukan "how many".',"Countable/Uncountable")
B.SG=new A.bK("There are many traffics in this city.","There is a lot of traffic in this city.",'"Traffic" adalah uncountable noun. Gunakan "a lot of traffic" atau "heavy traffic".',"Countable/Uncountable")
B.SI=new A.bK("She always is happy.","She is always happy.","Adverb of frequency (always, usually, often) datang SETELAH to be atau SEBELUM main verb.","Word Order")
B.T0=new A.bK("I have never seen such a thing.","I have never seen such a thing.",'Benar! "Never" sebagai adverb negatif ditempatkan setelah auxiliary.',"Word Order")
B.Th=new A.bK("She quickly finished her homework.","She finished her homework quickly.",'Untuk verb tunggal, adverb bisa di akhir kalimat. "She finished her homework quickly."',"Word Order")
B.T1=new A.bK("He is hardly working lately.","He is hardly working lately.",'"Hardly" adalah adverb yang berarti "hampir tidak". Untuk kata "keras/rajin", gunakan "hard".',"Word Order")
B.SW=new A.bK("I go to the school everyday.","I go to school everyday.","Ketika school, hospital, dll digunakan tanpa article, mereka merujuk pada fungsi umum (belajar, berobat), bukan bangunan spesifik.","Word Order")
B.SQ=new A.bK("Between you and I, this is wrong.","Between you and me, this is wrong.",'"Between" memerlukan objek pronoun (me, him, her). "I" adalah subject pronoun.',"Pronoun")
B.Tc=new A.bK("Me and my friend went to the cinema.","My friend and I went to the cinema.",'Letakkan orang lain terlebih dahulu. Gunakan "I" bukan "me" sebagai subject.',"Pronoun")
B.T8=new A.bK("Who do you think is calling?","Who do you think is calling?",'"Who" adalah subject dalam clause "who is calling", jadi tidak memerlukan "does".',"Pronoun")
B.SE=new A.bK("The book which I read it was interesting.","The book which I read was interesting.",'Jangan ulangi object dalam relative clause. "Which I read" sudah cukup, tidak perlu "it".',"Pronoun")
B.SK=new A.bK("His is a new car.","His car is new. / That is his car.",'"His" sebagai possessive pronoun tidak memerlukan noun setelahnya. Gunakan "His car" atau kalimat lain.',"Pronoun")
B.Tf=new A.bK("I didn't go because I was sick.","I didn't go because I was sick. (The comma is optional here)",'Benar. "Because" memerlukan negative clause. Jika maksudnya "saya tidak pergi karena sakit", kalimat ini benar.',"Conjunction")
B.SJ=new A.bK(u.x,u.x,'Dengan "neither...nor", verb \u0441\u043e\u0433\u043b\u0430\u0441nya \u0441 \u043f\u043e\u0441\u043b\u0435\u0434\u043d\u0438\u043c \u044d\u043b\u0435\u043c\u0435\u043d\u0442\u043e\u043c. "Students" plural, jadi "were" benar.',"Conjunction")
B.SC=new A.bK("I would like to go but I am busy.","I would like to go but I am busy.",'Benar! "But" digunakan sebagai coordinating conjunction untuk menunjukkan kontras.',"Conjunction")
B.SB=new A.bK("Although it was raining, but we went out.","Although it was raining, we went out.",'Jangan gunakan "although" dan "but" bersama-sama. Pilih salah satu.',"Conjunction")
B.SM=new A.bK("I will come if you will call me.","I will come if you call me.",'Dalam if-clause tipe 1, jangan gunakan "will". Gunakan present simple meskipun main clause menggunakan future.',"Conjunction")
